# Line-ending normalization: without this, Git's core.autocrlf setting can
# flip the whole working tree's line endings on checkout/commit (this
# happened once already and produced a 3776-line noise diff with no real
# content changes). These rules make line-ending handling explicit and
# repo-controlled instead of depending on each contributor's local Git config.
* text=auto

*.py  text
*.md  text
*.spec text

*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.db  binary
